edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.io

Class FacultyRecordIO

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.io.FacultyRecordIO

  • public class FacultyRecordIO
extends java.lang.Object
    This class processes files containing Faculty Records. Text files can be read and Faculty objects created from the information contained in the file. Text files containing a list of student records can also be created. If a file is unreadable, a FileNotFoundException will be thrown
    Author:
    kmbrown

      • readFacultyRecords

        public static ArrayList<Faculty> readFacultyRecords(java.lang.String fileName)
                                             throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Takes in the name of a text file containing faculty records, reads the file to access the records, processes those records to create Faculty objects, and returns an SortedList of those Faculty. Throws FileNotFoundException if the file is unreadable.
        Parameters:
        fileName - The name of the text file containing a list of faculty records
        Returns:
        an SortedList containing Faculty objects created from the information in the file
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if file cannot be located or read

      • processFaculty

        private static Faculty processFaculty(java.lang.String facultyRecord)
        Accepts an individual line of information from the file and processes it into a new Faculty
        Parameters:
        facultyRecord - the line of info containing the faculty's name, id, email, password, and max credits
        facultyRecord - String containing the line from the file to process as Faculty
        Returns:
        the new Faculty object
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if information is not in correct format
